    <stylesheets>
        <URL value="@Design/helpn.css" />
    </stylesheets>
    <children>
        <VBox layoutX="20.0" layoutY="20.0" spacing="10.0">
            <Label styleClass="title-label" text="Help - Absence Management Platform" />
            <Label styleClass="subtitle-label" text="How to Use the Platform:" />
            <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="760.0" styleClass="help-text-area" text="This platform helps you manage student absences in a middle school. Here are the steps to use the platform effectively: &#10;&#10;1. Search for a Student: &#10;- Enter the student's name or ID in the search field. &#10;- Click the &quot;Search&quot; button to find the student in the system. &#10;&#10;2. View Student Absences: &#10;- Once the student is found, their information will be displayed in the table. &#10;- The table columns show the student's ID, name, grade, and absence count. &#10;&#10;3. Add an Absence: &#10;- To add an absence for a student, click the &quot;Add Absence&quot; button. &#10;- Follow the prompts to enter the necessary details such as the date and reason for the absence. &#10;&#10;4. Edit or Delete Absences: &#10;- To edit or delete an existing absence, select the absence from the table. &#10;- Use the provided options to make changes or remove the absence. &#10;&#10;5. Save and Export Data: &#10;- The platform automatically saves changes to the absence records. &#10;- You can also export the absence data to a file for further analysis or reporting. &#10;&#10;For any further assistance, please refer to the documentation or contact the support team.">
                This platform helps you manage student absences in a middle school. Here are the steps to use the platform effectively:

                1. Search for a Student:
                - Enter the student's name or ID in the search field.
                - Click the "Search" button to find the student in the system.

                2. View Student Absences:
                - Once the student is found, their information will be displayed in the table.
                - The table columns show the student's ID, name, grade, and absence count.

                3. Add an Absence:
                - To add an absence for a student, click the "Add Absence" button.
                - Follow the prompts to enter the necessary details such as the date and reason for the absence.

                4. Edit or Delete Absences:
                - To edit or delete an existing absence, select the absence from the table.
                - Use the provided options to make changes or remove the absence.

                5. Save and Export Data:
                - The platform automatically saves changes to the absence records.
                - You can also export the absence data to a file for further analysis or reporting.

                For any further assistance, please refer to the documentation or contact the support team.
            </TextArea>
            <Button fx:id="closeButton" styleClass="close-button" text="Close" />
        </VBox>
    </children>
</AnchorPane>
